</ul></div>
<p>From <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.x.org/wiki/">http://www.x.org/wiki/</a>:
</p>
<dl><dd>The X.Org project provides an open source implementation of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X_Window_System" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:X Window System">X Window System</a>. The development work is being done in conjunction with the freedesktop.org community. The X.Org Foundation is the educational non-profit corporation whose Board serves this effort, and whose Members lead this work.</dd></dl>
<p><b>Xorg</b> (commonly referred as simply <b>X</b>) is the most popular display server among Linux users. Its ubiquity has led to making it an ever-present requisite for GUI applications, resulting in massive adoption from most distributions. See the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X.Org_Server" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:X.Org Server">Xorg</a> Wikipedia article or visit the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.x.org/wiki/">Xorg website</a> for more details.
</p>
